						<summary>

						<p>Pillar standing (reverse) in front of a <hi rend="italic">liṅga</hi> in a field to the west of the village.</p>						

						<p>This undated epigraph may be assigned to the 7th century A.D. on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It gives the epithet <hi rend="italic">Tribhuvanā-Singaṁbu.</hi></p>						

